        {
            "id": 1,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "As intracellular parasites , viruses require a host cell",
            "relation": "BACKGROUND"
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "in order to replicate . <S>",
            "relation": "ENABLEMENT"
        },
        {
            "id": 3,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "However , they face a series of cellular responses against infection . <S>",
            "relation": "COMPARISON"
        },
        {
            "id": 4,
            "parent": 3,
            "text": "One of these responses is the activation of the double - stranded RNA ( dsRNA)-activated protein kinase R ( PKR ) . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 5,
            "parent": 4,
            "text": "PKR phosphorylates the \u03b1 subunit of eukaryotic translation initiation factor 2 ( eIF2\u03b1 ) ,",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 6,
            "parent": 5,
            "text": "which in turn results in global protein synthesis inhibition and formation of stress granules ( SGs ) . <S>",
            "relation": "CAUSE-RESULT"
        },
        {
            "id": 7,
            "parent": 8,
            "text": "Recent studies have shown",
            "relation": "ATTRIBUTION"
        },
        {
            "id": 8,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "that SGs can interfere with the replicative cycle of certain viruses . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 9,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "This review addresses",
            "relation": "ATTRIBUTION"
        },
        {
            "id": 10,
            "parent": 0,
            "text": "how viruses have evolved different control strategies at the SG level",
            "relation": "ROOT"
        },
        {
            "id": 11,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "to ensure an efficient replication cycle during the cellular stress response",
            "relation": "ENABLEMENT"
        },
        {
            "id": 12,
            "parent": 11,
            "text": "triggered by the viral infection . <S> <P>",
            "relation": "CAUSE-RESULT"
        }
    ]
}